        <abstract> 
<p>Asks WHF to check over some enclosed MS pages [<hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>, 6th ed.?]. CD quotes some of WHF’s remarks, but should WHF not wish to be mixed with CD’s theoretic notions, CD will omit the whole paragraph.</p>  
<p>Many think CD’s notions are "rubbish, pleasantly flavoured", like the reviewer in the <hi rend="italic">Quarterly Review</hi>, who CD cannot doubt is "Mr Mivart, with bigotry arrogance illiberality &amp; many other nice qualities".</p> 
        </abstract>
